{
  "masechta": "Bava Batra",
  "daf": 169,
  "amud": "a",
  "macro_segments": [
    {
      "title": "The Braita on Lost Documents: Loan Documents vs. Sale Documents",
      "display_title": "Lost Documents Rule",
      "timestamp": "00:18",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Introduction to the Braita: When a creditor claims he lost his loan document",
          "display_title": "Braita Intro",
          "timestamp": "00:18"
        },
        {
          "title": "Why loan documents cannot be rewritten: risk of double collection",
          "display_title": "Why No Loan Rewrite",
          "timestamp": "00:42"
        },
        {
          "title": "Sale documents can be rewritten without achrayus (warranty)",
          "display_title": "Sale Docs Allowed",
          "timestamp": "01:05"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Mechanics of Achrayus (Warranty) and Double Collection Schemes",
      "display_title": "Achrayus & Liens",
      "timestamp": "02:03",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "How achrayus creates liens on all property the seller subsequently sells",
          "display_title": "Liens on Sales",
          "timestamp": "02:03"
        },
        {
          "title": "Double collection scenario: using two documents to collect from multiple buyers",
          "display_title": "Double Collect",
          "timestamp": "04:33"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Braita on Lost Documents: Loan Documents vs. Sale Documents (continued)",
      "display_title": "Lost Documents Rule (II)",
      "timestamp": "06:02",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabban Shimon ben Gamliel's dispute: even sale documents cannot be rewritten",
          "display_title": "RSG Disagrees",
          "timestamp": "06:02"
        },
        {
          "title": "The concern with RSG: returning the original document reverses the sale",
          "display_title": "RSG Concern",
          "timestamp": "06:26"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tosafos on RSG: seller can obtain duplicate shtar from different scribe",
          "display_title": "Tosafos Solution",
          "timestamp": "07:12"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Mechanics of Achrayus (Warranty) and Double Collection Schemes (continued)",
      "display_title": "Achrayus & Liens (II)",
      "timestamp": "09:30",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Safra's explanation: why two shtarot with achrayus cannot exist",
          "display_title": "Rav Safra Logic",
          "timestamp": "09:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "The creditor's role in authenticating seizure of property",
          "display_title": "Creditor Role",
          "timestamp": "10:53"
        },
        {
          "title": "The problem: having the creditor seize twice requires destroying earlier documents",
          "display_title": "Destruction Issue",
          "timestamp": "15:42"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Gemara's Response: The Seizure Process and Its Documents",
      "display_title": "Seizure Process",
      "timestamp": "16:57",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Nachman: every seizure document requires tearing up the original debt note",
          "display_title": "Tear Up Note",
          "timestamp": "16:57"
        },
        {
          "title": "Three-stage document process: tirfa, adrachta, and shuma",
          "display_title": "Three Stages",
          "timestamp": "18:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "Why claiming original ownership (not debt) allows re-seizure",
          "display_title": "Original Ownership",
          "timestamp": "22:22"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Acha's question: why wait years between collections instead of same day",
          "display_title": "Same Day Question",
          "timestamp": "23:49"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Proposed Solution: Receipt to the Seller and Its Problems",
      "display_title": "Receipt Solution",
      "timestamp": "24:56",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Suggestion to give seller a receipt invalidating any prior shtarot",
          "display_title": "Shovar Proposal",
          "timestamp": "24:56"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rejection: the seller could be leapfrogged and receipt becomes worthless",
          "display_title": "Leapfrog Problem",
          "timestamp": "31:06"
        },
        {
          "title": "Comparison to loan documents: why receipts work there but not here",
          "display_title": "Loan vs Land",
          "timestamp": "35:42"
        },
        {
          "title": "Land claimants satisfied only with land, not cash",
          "display_title": "Land Not Cash",
          "timestamp": "39:01"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Writing a Shtar Without Achrayus: Explicit Exclusion and Default Rules",
      "display_title": "Shtar Lo B'Achrayus",
      "timestamp": "40:08",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rava's position: achrayus is default unless explicitly excluded",
          "display_title": "Rava Default",
          "timestamp": "40:08"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Ashi's position: absence of achrayus means no warranty intended",
          "display_title": "Rav Ashi View",
          "timestamp": "40:08"
        },
        {
          "title": "Story of woman who sent agent to buy land without achrayus",
          "display_title": "Woman Story",
          "timestamp": "40:08"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Nachman: shtar without achrayus explicitly excludes warranty",
          "display_title": "Explicit Exclusion",
          "timestamp": "40:37"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Nachman's solution: rebuy from seller and resell with achrayus",
          "display_title": "Nachman Solution",
          "timestamp": "41:04"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Returning the Shtar and Reversal of Sale: The Core Dispute",
      "display_title": "Shtar Return Issue",
      "timestamp": "42:38",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabban Shimon ben Gamliel: returning shtar reverses the sale",
          "display_title": "RSG Reversal",
          "timestamp": "42:38"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chachamim disagree: returning shtar does not reverse the sale",
          "display_title": "Chachamim No Reversal",
          "timestamp": "42:38"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Assi's theory: ownership conditioned on holding the shtar",
          "display_title": "Conditional Theory",
          "timestamp": "42:38"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rava's objection: loss or theft of shtar should not reverse sale",
          "display_title": "Rava Objection",
          "timestamp": "42:38"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "The Nature of Kinyan: Transfer of Otiyos (Letters) by Mesira (Handing Over)",
      "display_title": "Kinyan by Mesira",
      "timestamp": "42:38",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "The core dispute: can handing over a shtar transfer property or debt",
          "display_title": "Mesira Transfer",
          "timestamp": "42:38"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rava's view: otiyos (letters) are acquired through mesira",
          "display_title": "Rava Position",
          "timestamp": "42:38"
        },
        {
          "title": "Application to karka: returning shtar to seller returns property",
          "display_title": "Return Property",
          "timestamp": "51:37"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chachamim's view: otiyos are not acquired through mesira alone",
          "display_title": "Chachamim Pos",
          "timestamp": "53:49"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
